  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Assist the Project Manager in planning, coordinating, and executing construction works related to <strong>chemical piping installation</strong> in semiconductor facilities.</li><li>Coordinate with main contractor, consultants, clients, and internal teams to ensure works are carried out according to <strong>project specifications, drawings, and schedules</strong>.</li><li>Prepare and review <strong>method statements, work schedules, shop drawings, and material submissions</strong>.</li><li>Monitor site progress, manpower deployment, and subcontractor performance to ensure timely completion of works.</li><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>safety regulations</strong>, quality standards, and project requirements.</li><li>Attend site meetings and prepare <strong>progress reports</strong> and technical documentation.</li><li>Support testing, commissioning, and handover activities.</li><li>Assist in resolving technical issues and site coordination matters.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Mechanical Engineering, or related discipline</strong>.</li><li>Preferably <strong>2–5 years of relevant experience</strong> in construction projects.</li><li>Experience in <strong>chemical piping mechanical works, or semiconductor facilities</strong> is an advantage.</li><li>Able to read and interpret <strong>engineering drawings and specifications</strong>.</li><li>Familiar with construction site coordination and documentation.</li><li>Good communication and teamwork skills.</li><li>Willing to work on construction sites.</li></ul>",
